This paper focuses on Reinforcement Learning (RL) algorithms and their application in video games, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of normalizing flows, which is a technique commonly used in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Robotics (cs.RO) research. Finally, the paper explores the impact of the algorithm on benchmark tasks, which could potentially fall under the category of Game Theory (cs.GT).
